  "market_context": "Silver on the 1-hour chart is trading at the sell side of the curve, having run out the lows including a sweep of the previous day low. Failure swings remain on the buy side, presenting unprotected liquidity targets above current price.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept the previous day low and then closed through the series of down-close candles that formed that low, creating a protected low. This change in state of delivery confirms the reversal and allows anticipating continuation higher into the failure swings above.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the sell side of the curve where price ran out the lows, including a sweep of the previous day low.",
    "Confirm the low is protected: price closed through the series of down-close candles that formed the swing low (change in state of delivery).",
    "Note failure swings on the buy side as the draw on liquidity / target since we want to trade toward failure swings with protected swings on our side.",
    "Zoom in to find a point of interest: a fair value gap with a down-close candle into it that is then closed over, forming a new protected swing / continuation order block at low-risk buy.",
    "Plan the entry at the order block / FVG POI with stop on the invalidation (protected low) for tight risk-to-reward.",
    "Target first 2R, then extend toward the buy side liquidity at the highs (failure swings)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade played out with continuation higher, reaching the take-profit at the highs (BSL).",
  "lessons": "Track protected swings — they define invalidation and where opportunities lie. You don't need to catch the reversal itself; the continuation entry after the change in state of delivery is confirmed offers tight risk and lets you trade toward failure swings on the opposite side.",
